
    World Falconry Day: Eagle and falcons soar over desert show

        

    
        Egyptian falconers have met in the desert near Alexandria to celebrate World Falconry Day and highlight an ancient sport.
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Yasser al-Khawanky fed his Golden Eagle at the gathering at Borg al-Arab.
                
            
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Golden Eagles have been kept for hunting for centuries.
                
            
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    The birds were lined up at sunrise for the celebration.
                
            
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    They soared through the sky to swoop on pigeons and rabbits in front of the spectators.
                
            
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Hunting with birds dates back to the ancient Egyptians.
                
            
                
